title: 21 die in crash after bus plunges from Venice overpass
description: A vehicle in mainland Venice broke through the flyover guardrails and plunged nearly 100 feet. The local mayor called it an “apocalyptic scene.”

title: U.S. charges Chinese companies, executives with fentanyl crimes
description: The charges were the second major set of indictments the Biden administration has unsealed since June accusing Chinese companies of supplying Mexican cartels.

title: A look at possible contenders for the 2023 Nobel Peace Prize
description: The Nobel Peace Prize, once focused on efforts to end war, increasingly recognizes work in human rights and providing succor to the oppressed and disadvantaged.

title: Schumer to lead bipartisan Senate delegation to China amid tensions
description: Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer will travel to China, Japan and South Korea with two other Democratic senators and three Republicans to advance U.S. interests.

title: Hitler’s birth house will become a police station to keep neo-Nazis away
description: Austria began to turn the house where Adolf Hitler was born in Braunau am Inn into a police station to keep it from becoming a neo-Nazi pilgrimage site.

title: Indian police raid critical media outlet over alleged China ties
description: The raids on NewsClick journalists come amid a pattern of government crackdowns against critical media outlets — including the BBC.

title: Compare your life expectancy with others around the world
description: Plug your age and gender into our life expectancy calculator to compare yourself with peers overseas. Find out why so many do better than in the United States.

title: Cream and sugar with your concrete? Australians add coffee to cement.
description: Scientists are trying to make concrete stronger and more sustainable by adding coffee grounds to the mix. Initial results are promising, but questions about scale remain.

title: It’s time for the 2023 Nobel Prizes. Here’s what you need to know.
description: Katalin Kariko and Drew Weissman, whose research is behind mRNA coronavirus vaccines, won the prize for medicine. The other laureates will be named this week.

title: WHO approves second, affordable vaccine in fight against deadly malaria
description: The World Health Organization reported an estimated 619,000 deaths in 2021 from malaria, which disproportionately affects children under 5 in Africa.

title: Ukraine live briefing: $5.2B in aid proposed after E.U. diplomats meet Zelensky in Kyiv
description: For the first time, European foreign ministers met in a country at war. The bloc’s foreign policy chief Josep Borrell proposed a bilateral aid package.

title: Asia’s youngest nation emerges as a voice of conscience on Myanmar
description: Two decades after winning its own struggle against a brutal and corrupt military, the small island nation of East Timor is backing the Myanmar resistance.

title: England’s most famous tree might regrow — but it could take a generation
description: Tree experts say the stump of the Sycamore Gap tree will probably regrow, but its comeback could take decades.
